OL,5, Hundreds of people have attended a     
OL,6, service of thanksgiving for former BBC 
OL,7, Look North presenter Harry Gration.    
OL,9,FThe long-standing broadcaster died at  
OL,10,Fthe age of 71 on 24 June.              
OL,12,FAddressing the congregation at York    
OL,13,FMinster, Mr Gration's widow Helen      
OL,14,Fthanked people for attending the       
OL,15,Fservice and described her husband as   
OL,16,Feveryone's friend.                     
OL,18,FIn addition to family, friends and     
OL,19,Fcolleagues, the public had also been   
OL,20,Finvited to attend the service.         
